    "html": "<div class=\"answer-capsule\"><p>Spire and Secureframe represent two approaches to SOC 2 automation in 2026 — Spire as an AI-native platform with automated evidence evaluation and Secureframe as a well-established platform with 300+ integrations and strong evidence collection capabilities. Secureframe was acquired by OneTrust in 2024 and operates as part of the OneTrust GRC suite. Spire competes by offering more advanced AI-powered features at a lower total cost for most B2B SaaS companies.</p></div>\n<h2>AI and Automation Approach</h2>\n<p>Spire's AI audit agent evaluates collected evidence against SOC 2 controls and produces structured readiness reports. Secureframe provides rule-based evidence collection with integrations to 300+ tools but lacks Spire's AI-powered evidence evaluation. Spire also provides AI questionnaire response automation that generates answers from your compliance evidence base.</p>\n<h2>Integration Coverage</h2>\n<p>Secureframe offers 300+ integrations — the broadest coverage after Vanta. Spire covers the essential integration set for B2B SaaS (40+ integrations). For companies with standard cloud-native infrastructure (AWS, GCP, GitHub, Okta), both platforms adequately cover SOC 2 evidence collection.</p>\n<h2>Pricing and Value</h2>\n<p>Secureframe pricing starts at approximately $15,000 to $20,000 per year for SOC 2 coverage, with higher tiers available through OneTrust for enterprise GRC. Spire offers competitive pricing with AI-powered features included at standard tiers.</p>\n<h2>Best-Fit Customer Profile</h2>\n<p>Spire is best for: companies wanting AI-powered compliance automation, teams that want automated evidence evaluation and audit preparation, and companies that prefer a focused, modern compliance platform over a large GRC suite. Secureframe is best for: companies wanting the largest integration ecosystem, organizations evaluating OneTrust GRC suite integration, and companies that prefer an established platform.</p>\n<h2>FAQ</h2>\n<h3>Does Secureframe's OneTrust acquisition affect customers?</h3>\n<p>Secureframe continues to operate as a standalone product within OneTrust's GRC portfolio. The acquisition has expanded Secureframe's enterprise capabilities but some customers report changes in pricing and support structure.</p>\n<h3>Which platform has better SOC 2 Type II readiness speed?</h3>\n<p>Both platforms enable SOC 2 Type II readiness in 6 to 12 weeks. Spire's AI audit agent may reduce the readiness assessment phase by automating evidence gap analysis. Secureframe's integration-rich approach may reduce integration setup time.</p>\n<h3>Do both platforms support custom control frameworks?</h3>\n<p>Spire provides flexible control mapping for custom frameworks and multi-framework alignment. Secureframe, through OneTrust, offers extensive enterprise GRC customization capabilities.</p>\n"
